SIMPLE: optimism
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Optimism
<hw>Op"ti*mism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>optimus</ets> the best; akin to <ets>optio</ets> choice: cf. F.
<ets>optimisme</ets>. See <er>Option</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Metaph.)</fld> <def>The opinion or doctrine that
everything in nature, being the work of God, is ordered for the best, or
that the ordering of things in the universe is such as to produce the
highest good.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A habitual tendency or a present disposition to take
the most hopeful view of future events, and to expect a favorable
outcome even when unfavorable outcomes are possible; -- opposed to
<ant>pessimism</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Optimist</ent>⟦br⟧
